HEADWORD: Autoclastic
<hw>Au`to*clas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Auto-</er>; <er>Clastic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Broken
in place; -- said of rocks having a broken or brecciated structure due
to crushing, in contrast to those of brecciated materials brought from a
distance.</def>⟦br⟧
